{"title": "Trading the green card dream for Singapore", "tags": "opinion", "timestamp": "2024-08-11", "content": "It was the aroma of Indian masala that did it. After 10 years of working in America, the unexpected fragrance of home-cooked dhal wafting from a rundown motel on the Kansas border in 2010 made me decide it was time to return home, to Singapore.\nReminders of what it means to be a Singaporean are hard to miss in the month of August. Flags, buntings, strains of Count On Me Singapore, Home and other National Day songs on a loop at shopping malls. The National Day Parade."}